summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Mali, reaffirms its commitment to the country's sovereignty, unity, and territorial integrity. It notes progress in implementing the Agreement on Peace and Reconciliation, but expresses impatience with persistent delays and stresses the need for increased ownership and prioritization. The Council decides to:

1. Renew until 31 August 2020 the measures set out in paragraphs 1 to 7 of resolution 2374 (2017);
2. Reaffirm that these measures apply to individuals and entities designated by the Committee;
3. Extend until 30 September 2020 the mandate of the Panel of Experts and requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Panel;
4. Request the Panel of Experts to provide a midterm report by 29 February 2020, a final report by 15 August 2020, and periodic updates;
5. Reaffirm the reporting and review provisions as set out in resolution 2374 (2017);
6. Remain actively seized of the matter.
